				\begin{document}$${{{{{{\rm{C}}}}}}}_{{{{{{{\rm{H}}}}}}}_{2}{{{{{{\rm{SO}}}}}}}_{4}}^{\ast }$$\end{document} = 26.8 wt%, and the mass transfer driving force of water absorption is nearly zero. If we increase the current density J to 70 mA cm−2, the steady-state concentration of sulfuric acid is increased to 46.7 wt%, 75% higher than the equilibrium one CH2SO4*\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
